 not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William Curzon was born about 1134, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with William CURZON."},"et":{"ABT 1134–":"umbes 1134–Surnud","1131–Male":"1131–Surnud","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1134–Female":"1134–Surnud","ABT 1155":"umbes 1155","ABT 1134":"umbes 1134","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","1131":"1131","NORFOLK, ENGLAND":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1134–":"noin 1134–Kuollut","1131–Male":"1131–Kuollut","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1134–Female":"1134–Kuollut","ABT 1155":"noin 1155","ABT 1134":"noin 1134","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","1131":"1131","NORFOLK, ENGLAND":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1134–":"environ 1134–Décédée","1131–Male":"1131–Décédé","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1134–Female":"1134–Décédée","ABT 1155":"environ 1155","ABT 1134":"environ 1134","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","1131":"1131","NORFOLK, ENGLAND":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Curzon est née environ 1134, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec William CURZON."},"de":{"ABT 1134–":"um 1134–Verstorben","1131–Male":"1131–Verstorben","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorben","1134–Female":"1134–Verstorben","ABT 1155":"um 1155","ABT 1134":"um 1134","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","1131":"1131","NORFOLK, ENGLAND":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Curzon wurde um 1134 in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit William CURZON mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"ABT 1134–":"about 1134–Desede","1131–Male":"1131–Desede","1155–Female":"1155–Desede","1134–Female":"1134–Desede"